If run in claude code, also check .rules-zed-provided, for zed-agents they are auto injected. 

Unless explicitly asked never create commits. You can stage files, so nix sees them though.

You must NOT read files inside of /binary-hashes/ or /source-hashes/ directories. They are autogenerated, and do not contain useful context.

when running nix builds please always pass max jobs = 6 max cores = 4 otherwise we will OOM

when building always set the timeout to >1h as building can take a very very long time. because of this always do all other checks to avoid building, and only build if asked to

whenever possible common shared code should be placed at the appropirate location for shared code. Boilerplate should be avoided by having sane default.
